# CyberJournal

A free, open-source cybersecurity learning resource built for students. Structured knowledge, clear explanations, no paywalls.

## What This Is

CyberJournal covers 12 areas of cybersecurity — from fundamentals to malware analysis — with articles organized by category and subcategory for easy navigation. Built by a first-year CS student in the Netherlands who wanted a better way to learn.

## Categories

- Fundamentals
- Network Security
- Red Team
- Blue Team
- App & Web Security
- Cryptography
- Identity & Access Management (IAM)
- Cloud Security
- Governance, Risk & Compliance (GRC)
- Forensics
- Malware Analysis
- Incidents

## Built With

- [Eleventy](https://www.11ty.dev/) — static site generator
- Plain HTML, CSS, and JavaScript
- Terminal-style code blocks with copy functionality
